content: Anyone else watching this and wanna chat in a thread about it?
Yes! Tim Walz understands what it's like to live in rural areas and small towns. fr. It's really nice to feel seen and represented for once on the big stage.
That's cool to hear. I live in a rural town now but not for most of my life, so I don't think I fully get it. Not raised in a small town.

Welcome to rural town life! It's just nice to not feel overlooked. And I'm sure there's lots of folks in many demographics that hopefully are feeling seen with Harris-Walz. I know I am on many levels.
